The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the Congress, requesting consideration of Fiscal Year (FY) 2024 Budget amendments for various departments and programs. The amendments include increased funding for the National Science Foundation STEM Education account, which will be offset by funds from within NSF and the Department of Agriculture. There are also amendments shifting funds within the Department of Defense for higher priority programs. The letter also includes FY 2024 Budget amendments for the Legislative Branch, which would decrease the overall discretionary budget authority by $17 million. The details of the proposal can be found in the enclosed letter from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.